  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. This unit evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The intended use scope — predicting normalized index of hemolysis within ±15% of bench measurements at 2500 RPM and 5 L/min operating point for pre-market submission support — is described in the bound requirement and claim prose. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all 13 credibility factors; 7 factors were formally assessed and 6 remain flagged as epistemic gaps. Despite gaps, the assessment team accepted the package under the Minimal profile given the low-risk decision context and conservative bounding assumptions documented in the decision record.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-cfd-requirement",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-claim-absolute-hil",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-bench-hemolysis-dataset-2022",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-velocity-dataset-2021"
  ],
